=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex9 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 111 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 110.9569
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.8197
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1742
  pitch_clarity: 147.8953
  inharmonicity: 0.4414
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -14.1146
  resonance_freq: 258.3984

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 9
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 9 ---
{ Saw.ar(LFNoise1.kr(1).range(100,[200,300])) }.play;
{ Saw.ar(LFPulse.kr(1).range(100,[200,300]).lag([0.1,0.2])) }.play;
